{"pageModel":{"attributes":{"id":"","name":"97361.dita","viewName":"DitaDetail"},"elements":{"ditaContent":{"name":"DITAContent","value":"<article id=\"administration\" class=\"topic concept\">\r\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\">Users</h1>\r\n<div class=\"body conbody\">\r\n<section class=\"section\">\r\n<h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">User roles and permissions</strong>\r\n</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p\">User roles and permissions in AI Defense provide secure and role-specific access to capabilities and insights. Currently, the platform supports two roles: <strong class=\"ph b\">Admin</strong> and <strong class=\"ph b\">Analyst</strong>.</p>\r\n<table class=\"olh_note\" border=\"0\" role=\"note\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"5%\" class=\"olh_note\" role=\"heading\" border=\"0\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<img src=\"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/esp/icons/icon-notes.svg\">\r\n<br> </td>\r\n<td border=\"0\" class=\"olh_note\">\r\n<div class=\"note__content\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">You can manage your AI Defense users and roles in Security Cloud Control. For instructions, see  <a data-scope=\"external\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://securitydocs.cisco.com/docs/scc/admin/95953.dita\" title=\"\">Managing Role-Based Access Control</a> in the Security Cloud Control user guide.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class=\"section\">\r\n<h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Roles and permissions</strong>\r\n</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p\">The <strong class=\"ph b\">Admin</strong> role provides full system access, including the ability to configure, manage, and control all aspects of AI Defense. Admins can view and modify data, system settings, user roles, and AI Defense features. They have complete authority over validation processes, runtime policies, and application management.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p\">The <strong class=\"ph b\">Analyst</strong> role is a management role with restricted access, focused on operational tasks. Analysts can perform validation tests, add applications, and manage assets. However, they do not have the ability to create or modify policies or manage users.</p>\r\n<div class=\"sectiondiv\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Permissions and scopes</strong>\r\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody class=\"tbody\">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Scope</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<figure></figure>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Admin</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<figure></figure>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Analyst</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<figure></figure>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Dashboard</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Assets</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Applications</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Validation</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Administration</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">Not enabled </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Policies</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">API Key Generation</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">Enabled </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">Not enabled </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Events</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View/Edit/Manage </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">App Discovery</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">View </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Integrations Management</strong>\r\n</td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">Enabled </td>\r\n<td headers=\"\" align=\"\">Not enabled </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class=\"section\">\r\n<h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Role assignment</strong>\r\n</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"ul\">\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Role assignments are managed by Admins only.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">By default, the first user in your installation is assigned the Admin role.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class=\"section\">\r\n<h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\">\r\n<strong class=\"ph b\">Integrations</strong>\r\n</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p\">Admins can check the connection status, edit and disconnect product integrations. These integrations seamlessly connect diverse systems and applications to enable smooth data flow, interoperability, and enhanced functionality across platforms. See  <a data-scope=\"local\" target=\"\" href=\"docs/ai-def/user/97378.dita\" title=\"List of integration instructions pages\">Integrations</a>.</p>\r\n</section>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>\r\n","ditaVal":"","format":"html"},"bookTitle":{"value":""},"shortDescription":{"value":""}}},"parameters":{"appId":"SccAiDefense","topicAlias":"AIUsers"}}